description: With more than 9,000 deaths, Spain has the second-highest number of fatalities caused by coronavirus.
title: Coronavirus: Spain's deaths pass 9,000 as infection rate slows
title_page: Coronavirus: Spain's deaths pass 9,000 as infection rate slows - BBC News
maintext: Wednesday's number of deaths in Spain was marginally higher than the 849 announced the day before, and the country has now seen more than 800 deaths for five days in a row. But health officials believe the latest 12% increase in daily infections is further evidence that the rate has stabilised.
